definition.text: this category encompasses equipment specifically designed for railway track maintenance and operations that do not include driving mechanisms. It includes various tools and apparatus used to support the upkeep and functionality of railway tracks, ensuring safety and efficiency in rail transport. The items in this classification are essential for track inspection, repair, and general maintenance activities, playing a crucial role in the overall infrastructure of rail systems. These assets may consist of specialized vehicles and devices that facilitate the monitoring and enhancement of track conditions, providing support to rail operations without being equipped with propulsion systems.

this category encompasses specialized machinery designed for the construction, maintenance, and operation of railway tracks. These machines are engineered to perform various functions essential to track management, including but not limited to laying, repairing, and inspecting rail systems. They are distinguished by their capability to operate on railway tracks, ensuring efficient and safe handling of track-related tasks. This classification includes equipment that may be self-propelled or require towing, and it plays a critical role in the overall functionality and safety of railway infrastructure. The machinery within this category is vital for ensuring the longevity and reliability of rail transport systems.

a category of railborne vehicles specifically designed for measurement and testing purposes within railway systems. These vehicles are equipped with specialized instruments and tools to assess various parameters related to railway infrastructure, such as track geometry, alignment, and condition. They are utilized to ensure operational safety, optimize maintenance practices, and enhance the performance of rail networks. This classification is distinct from other types of railborne vehicles that serve different operational roles, such as transportation, construction, or maintenance, thereby emphasizing the unique functionality of measurement and testing within the railway sector.

a specialized vehicle designed for rail transport, primarily used for the movement of personnel and equipment within the railway infrastructure. This type of vehicle is equipped to facilitate various operational tasks, ensuring efficient access to work sites along the railway network. It is distinct from other types of rail vehicles that serve specific functions such as transportation of tools, materials, or equipment, and is characterized by its ability to accommodate both personnel and necessary operational gear. The design of this vehicle prioritizes safety and accessibility for crew members engaged in maintenance or construction activities on the railways, contributing to the overall efficiency and functionality of railway operations.

a rail vehicle designed for transporting equipment and personnel involved in maintenance and repair activities on railway tracks. This type of vehicle is specifically equipped with features that facilitate the movement of tools, machinery, and support systems necessary for track maintenance operations. It is distinct from other rail vehicles used for various purposes, such as those meant for hauling cargo, providing living quarters, or serving as mobile workshops. The design and functionality of this vehicle prioritize efficiency and safety in maintaining railway infrastructure, enabling quick access to areas requiring attention.

a railborne vehicle designed specifically for the accommodation and rest of passengers or crew during rail transport. This type of carriage is equipped with sleeping facilities, providing comfort and privacy for individuals traveling over long distances or during extended rail operations. It is distinct from other rail vehicles that serve various operational or equipment-related functions, focusing instead on passenger comfort and relaxation. The sleeping carriage is typically part of a larger fleet, serving both passenger and operational needs within rail transport systems.

a type of railborne vehicle designed primarily for transporting supplies and equipment necessary for operations, maintenance, or support activities related to rail systems. This vehicle is specifically structured to accommodate various types of materials and goods essential for the functioning of rail services. It features compartments and systems that facilitate the secure storage and easy access to the transported items, enhancing operational efficiency in rail transport scenarios. The design and configuration of this vehicle are tailored to meet the specific logistical needs of rail operations while adhering to safety and regulatory standards within the rail industry.

a specialized vehicle designed for rail transport, primarily utilized for unique operational purposes that differ from standard railway cars. This category encompasses vehicles tailored for specific tasks, offering enhanced functionality and features that support distinct operational requirements. These vehicles are essential for specialized tasks within the railway system, providing unique capabilities not typically found in conventional rail transport vehicles. They may include adaptations for various roles, including but not limited to maintenance, support, or operational needs, ensuring efficient performance in specialized applications. The design and construction of these vehicles prioritize the requirements of their intended use, thereby facilitating effective and reliable rail operations.

Wagon designed for long-distance passenger transportation on rails with seating and often sleeping facilities, which is part of a train.

a type of railway carriage specifically designed to provide seating accommodations for passengers during rail travel. This variant is characterized by its focus on comfort and accessibility for travelers, offering a spacious interior layout conducive to relaxation and social interaction. Unlike other configurations, this particular type does not include specialized facilities such as kitchens, baggage compartments, or sleeping quarters. Instead, it prioritizes the seating arrangement and overall passenger experience, ensuring that individuals can travel comfortably over various distances while enjoying the scenic views from the windows.

preferred_name.label: Seatwagon with kitchen and lunch room

definition.text: a mobile unit designed for rail transport, equipped with seating arrangements and facilities for meal preparation and dining. This type of vehicle typically includes amenities that support both passenger comfort and catering services, creating a multifunctional space for travelers. It serves to enhance the travel experience by providing a dedicated area for eating and social interaction, distinguishing it from other transport units that may focus solely on seating or cargo. This particular design accommodates the needs of passengers seeking both transportation and dining options during their journey.

a type of railway vehicle designed primarily for the transportation of passengers, featuring a designated area specifically for storing luggage and other personal belongings. This vehicle is tailored to enhance the comfort and convenience of travelers by providing additional space for baggage, ensuring that their needs are met during transit. It is distinct from other railway vehicles by its unique configuration and amenities, which cater to the requirements of passengers who may need to travel with multiple items or larger luggage, thereby facilitating a more enjoyable travel experience. This classification encompasses various features and arrangements that differentiate it from other passenger and freight transportation vehicles.

a seating vehicle designed for rail transport that incorporates a dedicated compartment for mail storage and handling. This type of carriage is equipped to accommodate passengers while simultaneously providing secure space for the transportation of mail and parcels. The design and functionality focus on ensuring comfort for travelers while facilitating efficient mail delivery, distinguishing it from other types of rail vehicles that may prioritize different features such as dining services or specific cargo types. This type of carriage is essential for integrated transport systems, supporting both passenger movement and logistical operations.

a sleeper is a specialized rail vehicle designed to provide passengers with accommodations for overnight travel. It features sleeping compartments that are equipped with beds or berths, allowing travelers to rest comfortably during long journeys. This type of rail vehicle is distinguished from other passenger cars by its focus on overnight accommodation rather than seating or dining services. The design may include amenities such as private or shared bathrooms, climate control, and storage for personal belongings, enhancing the comfort of passengers while they travel by rail. The sleeper is an essential component of long-distance rail services, catering to the needs of those seeking a restful travel experience.

a type of railway carriage designed to provide dining services to passengers while traveling. Its interior is equipped with facilities for food preparation and serving, creating an environment for meals and social interaction. This carriage typically features seating arrangements that facilitate dining experiences, offering a unique atmosphere compared to other types of railway carriages. It is specifically designed to accommodate the needs of travelers seeking food and beverage services during their journey, distinguishing it from other carriages that serve different purposes, such as accommodation, seating, or transportation of goods.

a specialized rail vehicle designed to facilitate the transportation of passengers in a communal setting, providing seating arrangements that promote social interaction. This type of rail carriage is equipped with amenities that enhance comfort during travel, distinguishing it from other rail vehicles by its focus on social engagement and shared experiences. Unlike other types of passenger cars, this variant emphasizes the communal aspect of rail travel, catering to groups looking to enjoy their journey together. The design and features support a unique travel experience, making it suitable for various passenger needs while ensuring compliance with safety and operational standards in rail transport.

a type of rail vehicle specifically designed for the transportation of goods, typically featuring an open or enclosed space for loading and unloading cargo. This vehicle is characterized by its ability to carry various types of freight while being equipped with necessary mechanisms for secure attachment to railway systems. It is distinct from other rail vehicles that primarily serve passenger needs or have specialized compartments for different purposes. This classification encompasses vehicles tailored for efficient logistical operations within the rail transport sector, enhancing the movement of commodities over long distances.

a type of railway vehicle specifically designed for the transportation of luggage and personal belongings of passengers. This vehicle prioritizes storage capacity and accessibility, ensuring that baggage is securely stored during travel while providing easy access for passengers and crew. Unlike other variants that may include seating or dining facilities, this unit is solely focused on handling baggage, making it an essential component of passenger rail services that enhances the overall travel experience by efficiently managing luggage. Its design and functionality cater to the unique requirements of transporting personal items, distinguishing it from other types of railway vehicles that serve different purposes.

a specialized railway vehicle designed for the transport of mail and postal materials. This type of vehicle is characterized by specific compartments and facilities tailored to securely store and manage mail during transit. Unlike standard passenger or freight cars, it is optimized for the efficient handling, organization, and delivery of postal items, ensuring timely and secure transportation. This class of railway vehicle supports the logistics of mail services and is integral to the broader network of rail transportation, focusing on the unique requirements of postal operations.

a vehicle designed for railway transport, specifically structured to accommodate baggage and parcels while featuring a designated compartment for mail. This type of carriage is equipped to ensure secure and efficient handling of luggage and postal items, optimizing space for both types of cargo. It serves a vital role in logistical operations within the railway system, facilitating the movement of personal belongings and postal deliveries simultaneously. The design emphasizes accessibility and organization, allowing for a streamlined process in loading and unloading goods while maintaining the integrity of the transported items.

These vehicles are engineered to perform various tasks associated with farming, such as planting, cultivating, harvesting, and transporting agricultural products. They are characterized by their robust construction, specialized attachments, and capabilities that enhance efficiency in agricultural operations. This classification distinctly excludes vehicles that are primarily intended for urban transport, lifting or hoisting, aerial travel, rail transport, maritime activities, or specialized applications unrelated to farming. The items classified within this category may include various types of farming machinery that facilitate modern agricultural practices.

this category encompasses vehicles specifically designed for agricultural applications, focusing on those utilized in farming activities. It includes specialized machinery that enhances efficiency and productivity in agricultural operations. This classification is distinct in its emphasis on vehicles that facilitate various farming tasks, such as tilling, planting, and harvesting. The offerings in this category are engineered to meet the unique demands of agricultural settings, ensuring optimal performance and reliability in field conditions. These vehicles are essential for modern farming practices, contributing to the overall effectiveness of agricultural productivity.

Engineering vehicle specifically designed to deliver a high tractive effort (or torque) at slow speeds, for the purposes of hauling a trailer or machinery used in agriculture or construction. Most commonly, the term is used to describe a farm vehicle that provides the power and traction to mechanize agricultural tasks, especially (and originally) tillage, but nowadays a great variety of tasks

Combine harvester, or simply combine, is a machine that harvests grain crops. The name derives from its combining three separate operations comprising harvesting - reaping, threshing, and winnowing - into a single process. Among the crops harvested with a combine are wheat, oats, rye, barley, corn (maize), sorghum, soybeans, flax (linseed), sunflowers, and canola

Submarine tenders refers to a type of ship that supplies and supports submarines

In naval terminology, a destroyer is a fast maneuverable long-endurance warship intended to escort larger vessels in a fleet, convoy or battle group and defend them against smaller powerful short-range attackers

The term has been in use for several hundred years, and has had different meanings throughout this period. During the Age of Sail, the term cruising referred to certain kinds of missions independent scouting, raiding or commerce protection fulfilled by a frigate or sloop, which were the cruising warships of a fleet

Small, fast, agile and offensive warship armed with anti-ship missiles, gun and/or torpedoes. FACs are usually operated in close proximity to land as they lack both the seakeeping and all-round defensive capabilities to survive in blue water
Warship that serves as a seagoing airbase, equipped with a full-length flight deck and facilities for carrying, arming, deploying, and recovering aircraft

Large armored warship with a main battery consisting of large caliber guns. During the late 19th and early 20th centuries the battleship was the most powerful type of warship, and a fleet of battleships was vital for any nation that desired to maintain command of the sea
Type of aircraft carrier whose primary purpose is to operate helicopters. Helicopter carriers have been used as anti-submarine warfare carriers and amphibious assault ships
This refers to any of several types of warship, the term having been used for ships of various sizes and roles over the last few centuries

this classification encompasses waterborne vehicles designed for oceanic navigation and transportation. These vessels are characterized by their robust construction, ability to withstand harsh marine environments, and capacity for carrying various types of cargo or passengers over long distances. They are distinct from smaller or specialized craft, focusing on functionality and performance in open waters. The category includes diverse types of ships, ranging from those designed for passenger transport and leisure activities to those intended for commercial freight and specialized operations. All types within this classification are equipped to operate in international waters, adhering to marine regulations and standards for safety and efficiency in maritime operations.

Defines any sort of ship or vessel that carries cargo, goods, and materials from one port to another. Cargo ships are usually specially designed for the task, often being equipped with cranes and other mechanisms to load and unload, and come in all sizes
Vehicle transport ships are special versions of RORO vessels

This ship is designed to transport liquids in bulk. Tankers can range in size from several hundred tons, designed to serve small harbours and coastal settlements, to several hundred thousand tons, with these being designed for long-range haulage

RORO ships are vessels designed to carry wheeled cargo, such as cars, trucks, semi-trailer trucks, trailers, and railroad cars, that are driven on and off the ship on their own wheels or using a platform vehicle, such as a self-propelled modular transporter

Merchant vessel used to carry passengers and vehicles and cargo as well across a body of water. Most ferries operate regular return services. A passenger ferry with many stops, such as in Venice, Italy, is sometimes called a water bus or water taxi

Also known as bulk freighter or bulker this is a merchant ship specially designed to transport unpackaged bulk cargo, such as grains, coal, ore, and cement in its cargo holds. Since the first specialized bulk carrier was built in 1852, economic forces have fuelled the development of these ships, causing them to grow in size and sophistication. Today's bulkers are specially designed to maximize capacity, safety, efficiency, and durability

Container ships (sometimes spelled containerships) are cargo ships that carry all of their load in truck-size intermodal containers, in a technique called containerization. They are a common means of commercial intermodal freight transport and now carry most seagoing non-bulk cargo

Ocean liner is a passenger ship designed to transport people from one seaport to another along regular long-distance maritime routes according to a schedule. Ocean liners may also carry cargo or mail, and may sometimes be used for other purposes

Traditionally a sailing ship (or simply ship) is a sailing vessel that carries three or more masts with square sails on each. Large sailing vessels that are not ship-rigged may be more precisely referred to by their sail rig, such as schooner, barque (also spelled 'bark'), brig, barkentine, brigantine or sloop
Cruise ships are passenger ships used for pleasure voyages, where the voyage itself and the ship's amenities are considered an essential part of the experience

Also known as a fish processing vessel, a factory ship is a large ocean-going vessel with extensive on-board facilities for processing and freezing caught fish or whales. Modern factory ships are automated and enlarged versions of the earlier whalers and their use for fishing has grown dramatically
Livestock carriers are large ships used in the live export of sheep, cattle and goats. They are specially built new or converted from container ships

definition.text: this classification encompasses various types of railborne vehicles specifically designed for operational support, maintenance, and auxiliary functions within railway systems. It includes vehicles that facilitate construction, maintenance, and inspection activities, as well as those that provide accommodations and supplies for personnel. The category covers specialized vehicles that do not primarily serve as passenger transport or freight carriers but are essential for the efficient functioning of railway operations. This includes vehicles equipped for specific tasks, such as measuring and testing, as well as transport for tools and equipment. Additionally, it encompasses vehicles that support the operational needs of railway staff and enhance the overall functionality of the rail infrastructure.

this classification encompasses vehicles specifically designed to facilitate the transportation of track motor cars. These units are engineered to operate on rail systems, providing essential support for the movement of related machinery and equipment. Unlike other vehicles in this classification, which may serve various operational and logistical functions on railways, this category focuses on trailers that augment the transport capabilities of track motor cars. Such trailers are integral for enhancing operational efficiency in rail transport, allowing for the seamless movement of specialized equipment and ensuring that the necessary tools are readily available for maintenance and operational tasks on the rail network.

a vehicle designed for operation on railway tracks, primarily utilized for specific work-related tasks within the rail industry. This type of transport is equipped to carry personnel, tools, or materials necessary for maintenance, construction, or operational support. It is distinct from vehicles intended for transport of goods or passengers, focusing instead on enhancing the efficiency of railway operations by providing a mobile platform for various work functions. The design and features of this vehicle facilitate the execution of specialized tasks on the rail network, contributing to the overall functionality and safety of railway services.

this category encompasses vehicles specifically designed to support construction activities within a railway environment. These units are utilized to transport tools, materials, and personnel necessary for construction and maintenance tasks related to rail infrastructure. They are engineered to operate on railway tracks and are characterized by features that facilitate the efficient movement of equipment and supplies. The vehicles in this category differ from other similar types by their specialized design and functionality, which are tailored to meet the demands of construction projects, ensuring safe and effective operations on railways.

a specialized transport vehicle designed for rail systems, intended to carry tools and equipment necessary for various operational tasks. This type of wagon is optimized for efficiency and accessibility, allowing for the organization and secure transport of essential gear required in maintenance, construction, or operational activities within the rail infrastructure. Its design accommodates the unique requirements of rail operations, distinguishing it from other types of rail vehicles. The tool and gear wagon enhances productivity by enabling quick access to tools and materials at work sites, thus supporting the effective execution of rail-related projects and services.

a wheelset is a critical assembly in railborne vehicles, consisting of two or more wheels mounted on a common axle, designed to support the vehicle's weight and facilitate smooth movement along tracks. This assembly plays a vital role in providing stability, ensuring effective load distribution, and enabling the vehicle to maneuver effectively. Wheelsets are engineered to withstand various forces encountered during operation, including those from acceleration, braking, and track irregularities. They are essential components for ensuring safe and efficient rail transport, contributing to the overall performance and reliability of railborne vehicles.

a circular device, typically made of a durable material, designed to rotate on an axle and facilitate movement or transport. This item is an essential component in various types of railborne vehicles, enabling them to navigate tracks efficiently. It is characterized by its structural integrity and ability to withstand significant loads and environmental conditions. The design may include features that enhance performance, such as tread patterns for traction and materials that reduce wear. This classification encompasses all variations of this component that serve the primary function of supporting the vehicle's weight and providing a smooth, controlled motion along the rail.

a wheel tire is a circular, flexible component designed to encase and support the wheel of a vehicle, specifically in railborne applications. It provides traction and stability, enabling smooth movement over tracks while accommodating various environmental conditions. The design and material composition of a wheel tire can vary, tailored to meet specific performance requirements such as load capacity, durability, and resistance to wear. This component plays a crucial role in ensuring the safety and efficiency of rail vehicles, contributing to their overall operational effectiveness. Unlike other related components, a wheel tire is specifically engineered to interact with the rail surface, enhancing the vehicle's handling and performance characteristics.

a structure specifically designed to be mounted on the chassis of a railborne vehicle, serving as the upper part that accommodates various functions and systems essential for the operation and usability of the vehicle. This includes elements that provide protection, support, and housing for components such as seating, storage, and operational equipment. The design and construction of this structure are tailored to meet the requirements of railborne transport, ensuring compatibility with the underlying chassis while optimizing the vehicle's performance and safety. It plays a crucial role in the overall functionality and efficiency of the railborne vehicle.

a category that encompasses tools and equipment specifically designed for the process of shaping, smoothing, or finishing surfaces of materials used in the construction or maintenance of railborne vehicles. This includes items that facilitate both the application of material removal techniques and the enhancement of surface characteristics to ensure optimal performance and longevity. The tools in this category are distinct in function and application from other components utilized in railborne vehicle systems, which may serve different roles in vehicle operation or structure.
Ship types which carry out activities on the water or from the water primarily except the transport of passengers and goods or of warfare

Dredging is an excavation activity usually carried out underwater, in shallow seas or freshwater areas with the purpose of gathering up bottom sediments and disposing of them at a different location. This technique is often used to keep waterways navigable

Deep-sea vessel designed and used to lay underwater cables for telecommunications, electric power transmission, or other purposes. Cable ships are distinguished by large cable sheaves for guiding cable over bow or stern or both. Bow sheaves, some very large, were characteristic of all cable ships in the past, but newer ships are tending toward having stern sheaves only, as seen in the photo of CS Cable Innovator at the Port of Astoria on this page

Specialised marine vessel used in a number of specific offshore roles such as offshore drilling rigs, safety vessels, oil production platforms, and heavy lift cranes. They are designed with good stability and seakeeping characteristics. Other terms include semisubmersible, semi-sub, or simply semi

Special-purpose ship or boat designed to move and navigate through ice-covered waters, and provide safe waterways for other boats and ships. Although the term usually refers to ice-breaking ships, it may also refer to smaller vessels, such as the icebreaking boats that were once used on the canals of the United Kingdom

This vessel is a lifting surface, or foil, that operates in water. They are similar in appearance and purpose to aerofoils used by aeroplanes. Boats that use hydrofoil technology are also simply termed hydrofoils. As a hydrofoil craft gains speed, the hydrofoils lift the boat's hull out of the water, decreasing drag and allowing greater speeds

Research vessels carry out a number of roles. Some of these roles can be combined into a single vessel but others require a dedicated vessel. Due to the demanding nature of the work, research vessels are often constructed around an icebreaker hull, allowing them to operate in polar waters

this category encompasses all types of rail vehicles designed for transportation on tracks. These vehicles are specifically engineered to facilitate the movement of passengers or freight and are integral to rail transport systems. This classification includes various locomotive types powered by diesel, electricity, or steam, as well as specialized vehicles such as motor-coach trains and those used in metropolitan railway systems. Unique rail vehicles like cogwheel and cable railways, which operate on specific terrains or in urban environments, are also included. The focus is on vehicles that are primarily associated with railborne operations, distinguishing them from other types of rail-related vehicles and components.

a type of rail vehicle specifically designed for the propulsion and transportation of cargo or passengers, utilizing a diesel engine as its primary source of power. This category encompasses vehicles that are equipped with a diesel engine to generate traction and may include features tailored for both freight and passenger services. Distinct from other rail vehicles powered by alternative energy sources, such as electricity or steam, this classification highlights the unique operational characteristics and design parameters associated with diesel-powered locomotion on rail networks. The classification includes various configurations and operational capabilities that enhance efficiency and effectiveness in rail transport.

definition.text: a type of rail vehicle that is powered by electricity, typically utilizing overhead wires or an electrified rail system for propulsion. This category encompasses various configurations designed for different applications, including freight and passenger transport. Electrical locomotives are characterized by their ability to provide efficient and environmentally-friendly operations compared to traditional fuel-powered locomotives. They are commonly used in various rail networks, offering advantages such as reduced emissions and lower operational costs. This classification distinguishes them from other locomotive types that utilize alternative power sources.

a steam locomotive is a type of rail vehicle that is powered by steam generated from boiling water. It typically utilizes a boiler to create steam, which drives pistons or turbines to produce motion. This category encompasses various designs and configurations, including those used for passenger transport, freight services, and specialized applications. Steam locomotives are characterized by their historical significance, mechanical complexity, and the distinct sound and appearance associated with steam-powered machinery. They played a crucial role in the development of rail transport and are often regarded as iconic representations of the industrial age.

a type of rail vehicle designed for versatile operation, capable of being powered by multiple energy sources. This unit is engineered to facilitate efficient transportation across rail networks, providing flexibility in energy consumption to adapt to various operational requirements. It serves in both passenger and freight services, showcasing advanced technology for enhanced performance and reduced environmental impact. The design incorporates features that allow for seamless transitions between different power sources, ensuring reliable service in diverse conditions and settings. This classification includes vehicles that may operate independently or in conjunction with other railway systems.

a type of rail vehicle designed specifically for passenger transportation, characterized by its ability to operate on rail tracks with a coach-like configuration. This vehicle typically features a robust design to accommodate a significant number of passengers and often incorporates amenities for comfort during travel. Unlike other rail vehicles, it is distinct in its operational mechanism and intended use, focusing primarily on long-distance passenger transit. Its design and functionality may vary, but it is fundamentally distinguished from freight-specific models and other rail vehicles that utilize different propulsion methods or serve alternative purposes.

definition.text: a category that encompasses railway systems designed for urban transit, operating within metropolitan areas, and adhering to specific regulatory standards set by national authorities. These railway systems are typically characterized by their frequent stops, high passenger capacity, and integration with other modes of public transport. They are engineered to provide efficient, reliable, and sustainable transport solutions to urban populations, enhancing mobility and reducing road congestion. This classification distinguishes these railway vehicles from other types of rail transport that serve different operational purposes, such as freight or long-distance travel, and includes specific design and operational features mandated by federal regulations.

a type of rail vehicle designed specifically for the transportation of passengers or goods along a track that uses cogwheel technology to navigate steep inclines. This system employs a toothed wheel that engages with a cogged rail, providing enhanced traction and stability on gradients where traditional rail systems may struggle. Cogwheel railways are often found in mountainous regions, serving both functional and scenic purposes. They can operate with various power sources and are characterized by their unique engineering, making them distinct from other rail vehicles that rely on different propulsion methods or configurations.

Armed helicopter with the primary role of an attack aircraft, with the capability of engaging targets on the ground, such as enemy infantry and armoured fighting vehicles. Due to their heavy armament they are sometimes called helicopter gunships

Initially observation helicopters were limited to visual observation by the aircrew, and most helicopters featured rounded, well-glazed cockpits for maximum visibility. Over time, the human eye became supplemented by optical sensor systems. Today, these include low light level television and forward looking infrared cameras
Transport helicopters are used to ferry troops and supplies where the lack of an airstrip would make transport via fixed-wing aircraft impossible

Commonly known as a drone, as an unmanned aircraft system (UAS), unmanned combat aerial vehicle (UCAV), or by several other names, this is an aircraft without a human pilot aboard. Fighter aircraft that has been modified, or used primarily, as a light bomber or attack aircraft. It differs from bomber and attack aircraft primarily in its origins, as a fighter that has been adapted into other roles, whereas bombers and attack aircraft are developed specifically for bombing and attack roles

Warships usually belong to a navy, though they have also been operated by individuals, cooperatives and corporations

They are engineered to provide efficient, reliable, and sustainable transport solutions to urban populations, enhancing mobility and reducing road congestion. This classification distinguishes these railway vehicles from other types of rail transport that serve different operational purposes, such as freight or long-distance travel, and includes specific design and operational features mandated by federal regulations.

a type of rail vehicle that is powered by electricity, typically utilizing overhead wires or an electrified rail system for propulsion. This category encompasses various configurations designed for different applications, including freight and passenger transport. They are commonly used in various rail networks, offering advantages such as reduced emissions and lower operational costs. This classification distinguishes them from other locomotive types that utilize alternative power sources.

a steam locomotive is a type of rail vehicle that is powered by steam generated from boiling water. It typically utilizes a boiler to create steam, which drives pistons or turbines to produce motion. This category encompasses various designs and configurations, including those used for passenger transport, freight services, and specialized applications. Steam locomotives are characterized by their historical significance, mechanical complexity, and the distinct sound and appearance associated with steam-powered machinery. They played a crucial role in the development of rail transport and are often regarded as iconic representations of the industrial age.

a device designed to enhance the braking effectiveness of a vehicle by amplifying the force applied to the brake pedal. This component converts a small force exerted by the driver into a larger force, assisting in the application of the braking system. It typically operates using vacuum, hydraulic pressure, or electronic means to facilitate smoother and more responsive braking operations. This element is crucial for ensuring the safety and reliability of railborne vehicles, contributing to improved stopping power and overall vehicle performance. It is distinct from other components such as traction elements, structural parts, or other mechanical assemblies used in the vehicle's braking and operational systems.

a device specifically designed to assist in the movement or maneuvering of railborne vehicles, facilitating the effective handling of such vehicles during operations. This apparatus is engineered to enhance operational efficiency and safety while engaging with rail systems. It plays a crucial role in both maintenance and operational contexts, ensuring that vehicles can be positioned accurately and securely within rail yards or during transit. The design and functionality of this device are distinct from other components that serve different purposes within the rail vehicle assembly, focusing on the unique requirements of vehicle mobility and control.

a drag shoe is an essential component used in railborne vehicles, primarily designed to provide controlled friction against the rail surface during braking or deceleration. This device helps to enhance the braking efficiency and stability of the vehicle by creating resistance, which aids in reducing speed or stopping the vehicle safely. Drag shoes are typically made from durable materials that withstand high levels of wear and tear due to constant contact with the rail. Their design and functionality are distinct from other components like braking systems or structural elements, as they focus specifically on the interaction between the vehicle and the railway track to ensure safe and efficient operation.
